<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="17">Type.</emphasis>
Hab. in sylvis remotis et occidentalibus flumini 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="17">Mississippi</emphasis>
confinibus, versus regionem Illinoensium, 1787 or 1789, A. Michaux s.n. (holotype: P, photograph GH; isotype: P). According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Straley, GB" journalOrPublisher="Ann. Missouri Bot. Gard." pageId="2" pageNumber="17" pagination="381 - 424" publicationUrl="10.2307/2395256" refId="B4" refString="Straley, GB, 1978. Systematics of Oenothera sect. Kneiffia (Onagraceae). Ann. Missouri Bot. Gard. 64: 381 - 424, 10.2307/2395256" title="Systematics of Oenothera sect. Kneiffia (Onagraceae)." url="10.2307/2395256" volume="64" year="1978">Straley (1978)</bibRefCitation>
the type is labeled &quot;Ouest de Ohio, Route aux Illinois,&quot; but the plant is presumably from the southern Appalachians, in the Carolinas or Virginia where Michaux collected in June and July of 1787 and 1789.
</paragraph>
